 Ngqamakhwe - Ngqamakhwe police arrested a 37-year-old man for alleged rape of his sister, aged 28. "It is alleged that the victim was left with minor children by her mother on Saturday at about 09h00 at Xilinxa Village, Ngqamakhwe," said police spokesperson, Captain Jackson Manatha. "The suspect went to the house where the victim was. "The perpetrator accosted, overpowered the victim and raped her." Capt Manatha said that the case was reported at Ngqamakhwe police station and the suspect was traced and arrested on Monday. "He is appearing before the Ngqamakhwe Magistrate’s Court on Wednesday morning on a charge of rape." Eastern Cape Police Provincial Commissioner, Lieutenant General Liziwe Ntshinga, condemned the alleged rape and furthermore commended the Ngqamakhwe police for their swift action in arresting the suspect. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 